{"format": "tiptap/v1", "updatedAt": "2026-06-22T08:39:56.072Z", "doc": {"type": "doc", "content": [{"type": "image", "attrs": {"src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,", "alt": "Autograd — concept overview"}}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "What Autograd Is"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Autograd"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (automatic differentiation) is PyTorch's built-in engine for automatically computing gradients (derivatives). It's the system that makes training deep learning models possible by automatically calculating the gradients needed to update model weights via backpropagation."}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Conceptually, autograd keeps a record of data (tensors) and all executed operations (along with resulting new tensors) in a "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "directed acyclic graph (DAG)"}, {"type": "text", "text": "."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Why Autograd Matters in Generative AI"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Autograd is essential because:"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Problem Without Autograd"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Solution With Autograd"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Manually computing gradients for thousands/millions of parameters is impossible"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Automatically computes gradients for all parameters"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Complex neural network derivatives require chain rule across many operations"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Traces all operations and applies chain rule automatically"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Debugging gradient calculations is error-prone"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Dynamic graph makes debugging straightforward"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Training generative models (GANs, diffusion, LLMs) requires precise gradients"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Enables efficient optimization of loss functions"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "It simplifies gradient computation, automatically builds computational graphs, and is essential for backpropagation in deep learning."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "How Autograd Works"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Core Mechanics"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "PyTorch builds a "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Dynamic Computational Graph (DCG)"}, {"type": "text", "text": " as operations are performed, tracking relationships between tensors and transformations. This differs from static graphs in TensorFlow 1.x, offering greater flexibility."}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Two-pass process:"}]}, {"type": "orderedList", "attrs": {"start": 1, "type": null}, "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Forward pass"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Builds computational graph while performing calculations"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Backward pass"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (backpropagation): Automatically computes gradients through the graph"}]}]}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "import torch\n\n# Create tensors with gradient tracking\nx = torch.tensor([1.0, 2.0, 3.0], requires_grad=True)  # Enable autograd [web:11]\ny = torch.tensor([4.0, 5.0, 6.0], requires_grad=True)\n\n# Forward pass: autograd records operations\nz = x * y + 2  # Operation recorded in graph [web:12]\noutput = z.sum()\n\n# Backward pass: compute gradients\noutput.backward()  # Traverses graph backwards [web:17]\n\n# Access computed gradients\nprint(x.grad)  # Gradient of output w.r.t. x [web:13]\nprint(y.grad)  # Gradient of output w.r.t. y"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Enabling Gradient Tracking"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "To enable autograd on a tensor, set "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "requires_grad=True"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "# Enable gradient tracking\nx = torch.randn(3, 4, requires_grad=True)\n\n# Disable (default for input data)\ndata = torch.randn(3, 4, requires_grad=False)  # No graph constructed [web:11]"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Important"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Only tensors of floating point and complex dtype can have gradients."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Integration with Tensors and Modules"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "With Tensors"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Autograd traces all calculations made on tensors with "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "requires_grad=True"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "# Build computational graph\na = torch.tensor([2.0], requires_grad=True)\nb = torch.tensor([3.0], requires_grad=True)\nc = a * b       # c.grad_fn = MulBackward\nd = c + 1       # d.grad_fn = AddBackward\ne = d ** 2      # e.grad_fn = PowBackward\n\ne.backward()    # Chain rule applied automatically\nprint(a.grad)   # ∂e/∂a = 2*(a*b+1)*b = 2*(7)*3 = 42"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "With Modules (Neural Networks)"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "class Generator(torch.nn.Module):  # For GANs/diffusion\n    def __init__(self):\n        super().__init__()\n        self.fc = torch.nn.Linear(128, 256)  # Parameters automatically track gradients\n    \n    def forward(self, x):\n        return self.fc(x)\n\nmodel = Generator()\ninput_tensor = torch.randn(32, 128)\noutput = model(input_tensor)\n\n# Loss computation\nloss = output.mean()\n\n# Automatic backpropagation\nloss.backward()  # Gradients computed for all parameters [web:12]\n\n# Weight update\nfor param in model.parameters():\n    param -= 0.01 * param.grad  # Gradient used for optimization"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Autograd is essential for training neural networks, calculating gradients needed to update model weights."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Mental Model"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Think of autograd as a "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "smart spreadsheet that remembers every calculation"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":"}]}, {"type": "orderedList", "attrs": {"start": 1, "type": null}, "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "You enter numbers and perform operations (multiply, add, etc.)"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "It records: \"A × B → C, then C + 1 → D\""}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "When you ask \"what's the gradient?\", it traces backwards using the chain rule"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "It tells you: \"If you change A by 0.01, the output changes by X\""}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "This is exactly what you need for "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "gradient descent"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": knowing how to adjust weights to minimize loss."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Key Features"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Feature"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Description"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Dynamic graphs"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Graph built on-the-fly during execution"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Automatic differentiation"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Computes derivatives without manual math"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Chain rule application"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Handles complex multi-layer gradients automatically"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "GPU compatibility"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Works with tensors on CPU or CUDA"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Optimization support"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Integrates with "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "torch.optim"}, {"type": "text", "text": " for weight updates"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Common Pitfalls & Best Practices"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "# ✅ Clear gradients before backward pass\nmodel.zero_grad()  # Or loss_grad.zero_()\nloss.backward()\n\n# ✅ Use detect_anomaly() for debugging\ntorch.autograd.detect_anomaly()\n\n# ❌ Avoid in-place operations that break graph\nx.add_(1)  # Modifies x in-place, may lose gradient info\n\n# ✅ Handle non-scalar outputs properly\noutput = model(x)\nloss = output.sum()  # Must reduce to scalar before .backward()\n# output.backward()  # WRONG: non-scalar\n\n# ⚠️ Retain graph if backpropagating twice\noutput.backward(retain_graph=True)  # Default clears graph [web:11]"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Real-World Usage in Generative AI"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "In training a "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "GAN"}, {"type": "text", "text": " or "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "diffusion model"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "# Training loop\nfor batch in data:\n    # Forward pass\n    real_images = batch\n    fake_images = generator(noise)\n    \n    # Compute loss\n    loss_fake = discriminator(fake_images).mean()\n    loss_real = discriminator(real_images).mean()\n    total_loss = loss_real - loss_fake\n    \n    # Backward pass (autograd computes all gradients)\n    total_loss.backward()  # Gradients for generator & discriminator [web:12]\n    \n    # Optimizer uses gradients\n    optimizer.step()"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Autograd computes gradients for "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "all parameters simultaneously"}, {"type": "text", "text": " across the entire network, enabling optimization of complex generative models with millions of parameters."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Key Takeaways"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Autograd = automatic differentiation engine"}, {"type": "text", "text": " that computes gradients dynamically"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Builds "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "dynamic computational graphs"}, {"type": "text", "text": " as operations execute"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Enables "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "backpropagation"}, {"type": "text", "text": " for training deep learning models"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Set "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "requires_grad=True"}, {"type": "text", "text": " to enable gradient tracking on tensors"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Call "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": ".backward()"}, {"type": "text", "text": " on a scalar to compute all gradients automatically"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Gradients stored in "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": ".grad"}, {"type": "text", "text": " attribute of tensors"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Essential for "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "optimizing loss functions"}, {"type": "text", "text": " in generative AI models"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Dynamic graphs"}, {"type": "text", "text": " offer better debugging than static graph frameworks"}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Autograd is the engine behind deep learning's magic—it makes computing gradients for complex neural networks trivial, enabling practitioners to build sophisticated generative models without manual gradient calculus."}]}]}}